Class VerifyingValidator

  • public class VerifyingValidator
extends JInputValidator
    A JInputValidator that uses a standard InputVerifier to toggle a good/bad state.

        public VerifyingValidator(@Nonnull
                          JComponent component,

        Create a VerifyingValidator. This is the same as calling VerifyingValidator(javax.swing.JComponent, javax.swing.InputVerifier, com.alexandriasoftware.swing.Validation, boolean) with the onInput parameter false.
        Parameters:
        component - the component to verify
        verifier - the verifier to use
        invalid - the validation to use when the InputVerifier.verify(javax.swing.JComponent) method of the verifier returns false

      • VerifyingValidator

        public VerifyingValidator(@Nonnull
                          JComponent component,
                          @Nonnull
                          InputVerifier verifier,
                          Validation invalid,
                          boolean onInput)
        Create a VerifyingValidator. This is the same as calling VerifyingValidator(javax.swing.JComponent, javax.swing.InputVerifier, com.alexandriasoftware.swing.Validation, com.alexandriasoftware.swing.Validation, boolean, com.alexandriasoftware.swing.JInputValidatorPreferences) with a Validation that has type Validation.Type.NONE for the valid parameter and JInputValidatorPreferences.getPreferences() for the preferences parameter.
        Parameters:
        component - the component to verify
        verifier - the verifier to use
        invalid - the validation to use when the InputVerifier.verify(javax.swing.JComponent) method of the verifier returns false
        onInput - true if validation should occur on every change to input; false if validation should only occur on focus changes

      • VerifyingValidator

        public VerifyingValidator(@Nonnull
                          JComponent component,
                          @Nonnull
                          InputVerifier verifier,
                          Validation invalid,
                          Validation valid,
                          boolean onInput,
                          @Nonnull
                          JInputValidatorPreferences preferences)
        Create a VerifyingValidator.
        Parameters:
        component - the component to verify
        verifier - the verifier to use
        invalid - the validation to use when the InputVerifier.verify(javax.swing.JComponent) method of the verifier returns false
        valid - the validation to use when the InputVerifier.verify(javax.swing.JComponent) method of the verifier returns true
        onInput - true if validation should occur on every change to input; false if validation should only occur on focus changes
        preferences - the preferences to use to draw the validation icons
